How can we use the power of pictures at work?

3
0:00:08,000000 --> 0:00:08,990000
How can you visualize what you think, what you know,

4
0:00:12,000000 --> 0:00:12,990000
and make that accessible for others to improve collaboration?

5
0:00:17,000000 --> 0:00:17,990000
I have been obsessed with this question for 30 years,

6
0:00:20,000000 --> 0:00:20,990000
in 20 books, in 200 articles, in more than dozens of experiments.

7
0:00:25,000000 --> 0:00:25,990000
And what I found are amazing benefits that happen when you draw,

8
0:00:30,000000 --> 0:00:30,990000
when you use visualization software, when you sketch, when you doodle.

9
0:00:34,000000 --> 0:00:34,990000
You boost your creativity, you improve collaboration and communication,

10
0:00:38,000000 --> 0:00:38,990000
have better conflicts.

11
0:00:40,000000 --> 0:00:40,990000
And you also improve your decision quality

12
0:00:43,000000 --> 0:00:43,990000
when you visualize the information that you have.

13
0:00:46,640000 --> 0:00:52,760000
But what I also found was that many of us don't use the potential of visualization at all.

14
0:00:53,560000 --> 0:00:56,940000
We stick to old ways of presenting, of discussing.

15
0:00:57,740000 --> 0:00:58,640000
Can I ask you this?

16
0:00:59,680000 --> 0:01:04,460000
Who among you still loves standard presentation slides with bullet points?

17
0:01:04,940000 --> 0:01:05,180000
Who loves to sit through that? Okay, we have four people. Anyone among you still loves standard presentation slides with bullet points?

18
0:01:05,180000 --> 0:01:06,880000
Who loves to sit through that?

